            summary:
              "GenLayer is an AI-native blockchain protocol that serves as a synthetic jurisdiction \u2014 a decentralized trust layer where validator nodes powered by diverse AI models reach consensus on subjective decisions. Unlike traditional blockchains that only process deterministic logic and numerical data, GenLayer can interpret natural language, evaluate qualitative evidence, and make nuanced judgments. It was designed to fill the gap left by conventional smart contract platforms: the inability to handle ambiguity, context, and real-world complexity without centralized oracles or human intervention. GenLayer\u2019s vision is to become the adjudication layer for the agentic economy \u2014 where AI agents can transact, dispute, and settle agreements at machine speed with trustless, impartial enforcement.\n\nAt its core, GenLayer introduces the concept of Intelligent Contracts, which are written in Python and can access the internet directly, process unstructured data such as text and images, and leverage AI inference during execution. This is a fundamental departure from traditional smart contracts that operate on fixed, deterministic inputs. The network achieves consensus through a mechanism called Optimistic Democracy, where validator nodes running different AI models independently verify execution results before accepting them. This multi-model approach significantly reduces the risk of bias or manipulation that could arise from relying on any single AI system.\n\nThe implications of GenLayer\u2019s architecture extend far beyond simple cryptocurrency transactions. By enabling subjective decision-making on a trustless network, GenLayer opens the door to entirely new categories of decentralized applications. Autonomous dispute resolution, AI-governed DAOs, decentralized arbitration, and self-settling prediction markets all become feasible for the first time. The platform effectively creates a programmable legal system that can operate at machine speed, resolving disputes and enforcing agreements without human courts or intermediaries.\n\nFor developers and entrepreneurs, GenLayer represents a paradigm shift in what blockchain can achieve. Instead of being limited to numerical operations and rigid logic, smart contract developers can now build applications that understand context, evaluate quality, and make judgments. This positions GenLayer as a critical infrastructure layer for the emerging agentic economy, where AI agents will increasingly need a neutral, trustless framework to negotiate, transact, and resolve disputes autonomously.",
